description:
An exceptional penthouse condominium in a boutique 3-unit 2009 building located on a prime block in the highly desirable Russian Hill neighborhood. The two-bedroom, two-bathroom residence showcases quality construction, high-end finishes, an exclusive-use roof deck with spectacular views, and a contemporary layout with an open floor plan and gourmet kitchen. The large bay windows let in a flood of natural sunlight and have picturesque views spanning Mount Tamalpais and the San Francisco Bay overlooking the historic Alcatraz Island and Ghiradelli Square Clocktower. Enjoy watching the power boats, sailing vessels, and cruise ships glide by! The residence is complete with hardwood floors, radiant heat, and side-by-side garage parking with interior access. Experience living steps from the recently completed Francisco Park - which provides some of the most famous views of the Bay and has a large picnic area, children's playground, and dog park - Aquatic Park, the Marina, North Beach, Ghiradelli Square and all of the shops, restaurants and attractions they offer.

FEATURES
* 2 Level 2BR/2BA 
* Approx. 1,282
* Open living room with large Bay windows
** Modern kitchen with custom cabinetry, under-mount lighting, premium stainless steel appliances
* Exclusive Roof deck
* Luxurious bathrooms 
*Radiant floor heating
* In-unit washer and dryer

RENTAL TERMS
* 1 Year Lease minimum
* Rent: $6,400
* Available: Now
* Security Deposit: $9,600
* Garage Parking - 1 Space
* 1 pet is allowed, breed restrictions apply
* Utilities: water and garbage included

APPLICATION
Please provide the below documents to be considered for tenancy. Applications will be considered on a first-come/first-served basis.
* $40 payable online to BanCal Property Management, for credit and background check (each applicant)
* Proof of income: two most recent pay stubs OR new employment letter (can be attached to online application)
* Copy of your photo ID (can be attached to online application)

BanCal Property Management - CA BRE 01313576
Equal Housing Opportunity

Introducing this brand new home on the 27th floor of the MIRA building, with full bridge and water views from the living room and 2nd bedroom and city skyline views from the main bedroom. With only 5 units in the building offering these remarkable views, this is a rare opportunity not to be missed! This fully upgraded residence boasts expensive wood floors, motorized shades, closet organizers, and a custom-built closet. Designed by award-winning architecture firm Studio Gang, MIRA is an iconic addition to the San Francisco skyline. MIRA features unique architecture with classic bay windows and striking views. Unbeatable location right across from Embarcadero waterfront and just a short walk away from world-class restaurants, coffee shops, Farmers Market, the Ferry Building, and Bay Bridge. SF Giants and Warriors stadiums are within walking distance, with easy access to all major freeways and public transit.

Sunny Mission 1BR/1BA condo on the vibrant Valencia Street corridor. Unit is located on the quieter 23rd street side of the building with floor to ceiling windows. The building is newer construction with dedicated bike parking, a large common roof deck with BBQ and lots of seating, ideal for entertaining. Latch keyless locks throughout. Unit is unfurnished (photos are staged). Neighborhood has amazing restaurants, bars and shopping with a 100 walk score, 83 transit score and 97 bike score.

Rent includes gas, water and garbage. Renter is responsible for all other utilities. No smoking/vaping in unit or anywhere on the property. One assigned bike parking space included. No vehicle parking. Renter must abide by all other 1188 Valencia Community Guidelines as outlined in the community handbook. Renters insurance required.

Introducing the epitome of luxurious city living at the Infinity a full-service building with city views. This exquisite 1BR/1BA + Den unit features beautiful hardwood floors, custom window treatments, a spacious walk-in closet with custom closet organizers, and sleek Studio Becker cabinetry. The kitchen boasts top-of-the-line Bosch & Thermador appliances, perfect for culinary enthusiasts, while the convenience of an in-unit washer dryer adds a touch of elegance. Renowned International Superstar Architect Bernardo Fort-Brescia of Arquitectonica, together with local powerhouse Heller Manus, has created an unparalleled living experience along San Francisco's waterfront. Prepare to be spoiled by an impressive array of luxury amenities, including a 24-hour doorman and concierge, a club room for entertaining, a 5,000-square-foot state-of-the-art gym for fitness enthusiasts, a refreshing 75-foot lap pool, a theatre room for movie nights, and a convenient business center for professionals. Just 2 blocks from the Embarcadero, Financial District, Ferry Building, Oracle Park, and some of the best restaurants and shopping spots the city has to offer. Easy access to the Bay Bridge, 80/101 and 280 Hways.

This exceptional condo sits high atop Telegraph Hill in a contemporary building. The fabulous views of the Bay Bridge, Treasure Island and the Transamerica building are matched only by the size of this expansive one bedroom. Complete with 3 massive closets, this unit also boasts a newly-renovated eat-in kitchen and bar area as well as a new bathroom.  The kitchen is fully equipped with stainless steel appliances and plenty of cabinet space. Capping it off, is your own private deck adjoining the living room and bedroom with city and bay views. And if that s not enough, there are 2 enormous shared decks, complete with BBQ and party space. And finally, one parking space is included, as are most utilities, and washer/dryers are just down the hall.  

Conveniently located within walking distance to the Financial District, Coit Tower, Waterfront and North Beach cafes and stores, this condo is ideal for those who work downtown or need quick and easy access to highways.

Welcome to 950 Tennessee Apartments, where comfort and convenience enhance your San Francisco lifestyle living. Our San Francisco, CA, apartments feature everything you need to live comfortably and stylishly in a place that feels like home as soon as you walk through the door. Get a taste of the thriving Dogpatch neighborhood that surrounds you with easy access to public transit and a range of dive bars, locally owned restaurants, sprinkled in with the best creative scene and night life entertainment for art and music lovers. At 950 Tennessee, you'll enjoy the ideal balance of outdoor adventure and modern city life. Take advantage of the city's attractions like SF's champion sports arenas Chase Center and AT&T Park and all the fun you'll experience living in the Bay Area. Visit the very popular food truck, beer & sangria garden at Spark Social SF for variety bites to eat, and then wind down and take in the breathtaking views in your brand-new home! Live at 950 Tennessee for the vibrant lifestyle you've been looking for. Welcome home!

A modern and stylish condominium in vibrant San Francisco, California. Situated in a prime location, this residence offers 2 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms, providing a comfortable living space for individuals. With a total area of 1,058 square feet, this condo presents a perfect blend of functionality and contemporary design.

As you step inside, you'll see the living area that is bright and open, featuring large windows that allow natural light to flood the space and a mesmerizing view of the sea. Adjacent to it is the dining and kitchen area which is well-appointed with stainless steel appliances, sleek granite countertops, tile backsplash, and white cabinetry with ample cabinet space for storage.

The primary suite is a peaceful sanctuary with an en-suite bathroom and a spacious closet. An additional bedroom offers flexibility, whether used as a guest room, home office, or a dedicated space for hobbies. The bathrooms are elegantly designed, featuring high-quality fixtures and finishes. The unit also includes a laundry area for added convenience.

Other amenities include central heating and air conditioning, an in-unit washer/dryer, and 1 dedicated parking space in the secured garage. The Malloch Building in Telegraph Hill is an iconic example of Streamline Modern Art Deco architecture. Unit #9 is just below the penthouse unit and features stunning views of the East Waterfront and Treasure Island. Located in the Cole Valley neighborhood and just half a block from Golden Gate Park, this fully updated condo offers the feeling of small-town living in the heart of San Francisco.
